    <body>
        <p>Lingo lets you use a concordance to perform advanced searches in one or more<MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Snippets.Snippet1"> translation memory (TM)</MadCap:conditionalText><MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Snippets.Snippet2"> TM</MadCap:conditionalText> databases. You can also search suggestions from<MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Snippets.Snippet3"> machine translation (MT)</MadCap:conditionalText><MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Snippets.Snippet4"> MT</MadCap:conditionalText> providers. This means you can search for words you've already translated to maintain consistency. The concordance searches the TM and suggestions from MT; in contrast, the search filter in the Translation Editor looks only in the current file.</p>
